30/07/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- The Olympic Village was inaugurated Thursday (29 July) at a ceremony attended by Athens 2004 President Gianna Angelopoulos-Daskalaki, Athens 2004 Executive Director Marton Simitsek, and International Olympic Committee Games Executive Director Gilbert Felli.
The village will host 16,000 athletes and their escorts during next month's Summer Olympics.
Organisers announced that Ioannis Manos, a member of the Full Board of Athens 2004, will serve as mayor of the village.
(ANA - 29/07/04)
